
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Protection";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Protection</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/wwwroot/css/Protection1.css">
    <script src="~/wwwroot/js/nav.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="box">

        <section>
            <div class="Welcome">
                <a>@Html.ActionLink("About us >> Homepage", "Index", "Home", new { area = "" }, new { @class = "nav-link" })</a>
            </div>

            <!-- <div class="center"></div> -->

            <div class="bottom">
                <h1>Ways to Contribute to Environmental Protection:</h1>
                <div class="choose">
                    <ul>
                        <li class="active">Reduce, Reuse, Recycle</li>
                        <li>Conserve Energy</li>
                        <li>Reduce Water Consumption</li>
                        <li>Use Public Transport and Carpool</li>
                        <li>Reduce Single-Use Plastics</li>
                        <li>Support Sustainable Practices</li>
                        <li>Plant Trees and Maintain Green Spaces</li>
                        <li>Advocate for Environmental Policies</li>
                        <li>Educate Yourself and Others</li>
                        <li>Reduce Meat Consumption</li>
                        <li>Minimize Food Waste</li>
                        <li>Dispose of Hazardous Materials Properly</li>
                    </ul>
                    <ol>
                        <li class="active">
                            <p>
                                Embrace the three "R's" to minimize waste and conserve resources. Reduce your
                                consumption,
                                reuse items whenever possible, and recycle materials like paper, plastic, and glass.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Be mindful of energy use by turning off lights and appliances when not in use. Consider
                                using energy-efficient appliances and opt for renewable energy sources whenever
                                possible.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Conserve water by fixing leaks, using low-flow fixtures, and avoiding wasteful practices
                                like leaving taps running unnecessarily.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Reduce carbon emissions by opting for public transportation, carpooling, or even biking or
                                walking for shorter trips.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Minimize your use of single-use plastics such as bags, bottles, and straws. Switch to
                                reusable alternatives.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Choose products and companies that follow sustainable and eco-friendly practices. Look for
                                certifications like Fair Trade or USDA Organic.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Participate in tree-planting initiatives and help maintain local parks and green spaces,
                                which contribute to cleaner air and biodiversity.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Get involved in environmental advocacy groups and support policies that promote
                                sustainability, clean energy, and environmental protection.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Stay informed about environmental issues and share knowledge with your community. Education
                                is a powerful tool for change.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Consider reducing your meat consumption, as the meat industry has a significant
                                environmental impact. Reducing meat in your diet can lower greenhouse gas emissions.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Plan meals efficiently and avoid wasting food. Composting organic waste can also reduce
                                landfill contributions.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Safely dispose of hazardous materials such as batteries and electronic waste at designated
                                collection points.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <script src="~/wwwroot/js/choose.js"></script>
                </div>
                <!-- <div>By incorporating these practices into your daily life, you can play a crucial role in preserving the environment and mitigating the impact of climate change. It's a collective effort that can lead to a more sustainable and healthier planet for future generation.</div> -->
            </div>

        </section>
    </div>
</body>

</html>

